comment: Lemma for ~ prmrec . If the series ` F ` was convergent, there would be some ` k ` such that the sum starting from ` k + 1 ` sums to less than ` 1 / 2 ` ; this is a sufficient hypothesis for ~ prmreclem5 to produce the contradictory bound ` N / 2 < ( 2 ^ k ) sqrt N ` , which is false for ` N = 2 ^ ( 2 k + 2 ) ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 6-Aug-2014.)
